1
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,910
[Deep Lurk]

2
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:37,830
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:42,130
[Flowers in the Mirror]

4
00:01:41,130 --> 00:01:42,390
This is the cipher key.

5
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,720
There should also be a codebook.

6
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:47,479
I sent Kawashima back to that small inn again.

7
00:01:47,550 --> 00:01:49,479
All of Myna's belongings are gone.

8
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:50,710
The innkeeper said

9
00:01:50,789 --> 00:01:52,890
that the things were taken by two young people.

10
00:01:52,890 --> 00:01:55,170
It must be Yun Hongshen and Yun Hongqi.

11
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,190
Hongqi,

12
00:02:37,510 --> 00:02:38,470
after I leave,

13
00:02:39,130 --> 00:02:40,860
you'll take care of the family.

14
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,160
Dad, I'm still worried.

15
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:45,350
I'm afraid I can't do it.

16
00:02:45,450 --> 00:02:46,810
The Yun family in my hands...

17
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:47,490
Hongqi,

18
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:49,430
you're overthinking it.

19
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:51,590
A family's prestige

20
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:53,660
isn't built by business operations alone.

21
00:02:53,660 --> 00:02:55,230
It relies on its family values

22
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:56,390
and its legacy.

23
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,880
Keep your heart pure,

24
00:02:58,190 --> 00:02:59,790
and your conduct righteous.

25
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:02,060
You are a descendant of the Yun family

26
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:03,140
and my son.

27
00:03:03,630 --> 00:03:05,230
I believe you will do well.

28
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,350
Dad.

29
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,190
I can definitely do it.

30
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:37,310
I'm sure I can.

31
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:47,470
You can't sleep either, huh?

32
00:03:48,950 --> 00:03:49,750
You too?

33
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:53,400
I'm thinking about something.

34
00:03:54,550 --> 00:03:55,340
Actually,

35
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:58,150
I was thinking...

36
00:03:58,550 --> 00:03:59,680
how about tomorrow,

37
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:02,000
we go fishing?

38
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:07,680
Hongqi,

39
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:11,550
let's talk outside.

40
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:12,080
Alright.

41
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:30,170
First thing tomorrow morning, I'll call the newspaper.

42
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:33,320
I'll tell them I'm a witness to the murder

43
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,490
at the Good Time Cafe

44
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,870
and want to provide them with a tip.

45
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:40,730
You're trying to lure the murderer out, aren't you?

46
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,350
What does this murderer

47
00:04:42,350 --> 00:04:43,650
have to do with Dad?

48
00:04:44,180 --> 00:04:46,550
I suspect the murderer who plotted to kill Dad

49
00:04:46,550 --> 00:04:48,480
must be a Japanese spy

50
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:50,170
who has been hiding in Changsha.

51
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:51,770
The murderer who killed Myna

52
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:53,730
should also be Japanese.

53
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:55,570
I see.

54
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:58,270
This murderer and this spy

55
00:04:58,270 --> 00:04:59,710
are likely connected.

56
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:01,110
If we find this murderer,

57
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:03,310
we can trace it back to the person who killed Dad.

58
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:04,110
Is that right?

59
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,270
That's correct.

60
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:07,030
Then your tip needs to be accurate

61
00:05:07,030 --> 00:05:08,670
to lure the murderer out.

62
00:05:08,790 --> 00:05:10,390
Making things up won't work.

63
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,320
The murderers should be two men.

64
00:05:14,030 --> 00:05:15,630
From the patterns and texture of the shoe soles

65
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:17,830
and the smell of Punch cigarss throughout the room,

66
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,560
I can pretty much conclude that

67
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,710
one was well-dressed,

68
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:23,170
and the other might have been his attendant.

69
00:05:23,270 --> 00:05:25,200
They came in through the back door.

70
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,790
This also indicates that

71
00:05:27,010 --> 00:05:29,540
the murderer might be a person of some renown.

72
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:31,950
Therefore, he wouldn't risk

73
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:33,830
being recognized by others.

74
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:43,200
I've practically watched you grow up.

75
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,930
I've seen you play chess with many people.

76
00:05:47,210 --> 00:05:49,470
But I've never seen you like this before,

77
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:52,240
struggling so much to make a move.

78
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:55,909
This move

79
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:58,350
is to venture deep into rival territory alone.

80
00:05:58,350 --> 00:06:00,010
I fear there may be no way back,

81
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:02,110
so I don't dare to make the decision.

82
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:07,110
When your Uncle Yun was alive,

83
00:06:07,390 --> 00:06:10,450
do you know why he was determined to establish a school?

84
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:13,950
He always had a lifelong wish:

85
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,100
to keep the sound of learning alive,

86
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:19,230
and to pass on knowledge from generation to generation.

87
00:06:19,340 --> 00:06:23,170
Shen grew up listening to these teachings.

88
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:24,740
In his heart,

89
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:27,750
there is a spirit of inheritance.

90
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:31,310
And Shen's chess playing

91
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:33,190
was also taught by Muzhi.

92
00:06:33,670 --> 00:06:36,600
Although his chess skills are not as good as Muzhi's,

93
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,600
he has the determination

94
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:40,590
to play this game well.

95
00:06:41,350 --> 00:06:42,310
I believe

96
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:45,710
he will pass down his grandfather's teachings

97
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:48,909
and the chess skills taught by Muzhi.

98
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:50,630
He has this aspiration,

99
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:52,510
and I'm truly gratified.

100
00:06:53,470 --> 00:06:55,330
As a descendant of the Yun family,

101
00:06:56,060 --> 00:06:57,860
this is also what he should do.

102
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:11,130
Hello.

103
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:12,070
I'm

104
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:14,930
a witness to the murder at Good Time Cafe yesterday.

105
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:17,320
Did you see clearly?

106
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:18,470
What?

107
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:20,120
There were two killers?

108
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,950
We will certainly compensate you for your help.

109
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:23,750
Alright,

110
00:07:23,770 --> 00:07:24,900
let's meet and talk.

111
00:07:26,150 --> 00:07:28,150
There's a witness for the cafe case?

112
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:29,150
Yes,

113
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:30,870
he asked to meet me at Hongyun Tea House.

114
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:31,950
Congratulations!

115
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:34,430
This bizarre murder case has caused quite a stir.

116
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,710
If you can get an exclusive,

117
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:37,970
you'll become the star of our newspaper.

118
00:07:38,550 --> 00:07:40,280
I hope your words bring me luck.

119
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,300
There shouldn't be any witnesses.

120
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:50,960
We deliberately parked the car at the bar on the next street

121
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,280
and walked to the cafe.

122
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:54,390
After reaching the back door,

123
00:07:54,770 --> 00:07:56,080
I repeatedly observed

124
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,460
that no one noticed us.

125
00:07:58,850 --> 00:08:00,330
There shouldn't be any,

126
00:08:00,470 --> 00:08:02,710
but that doesn't mean there really weren't any.

127
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:05,630
At least he's right about two people.

128
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:08,110
Go and take care of this.

129
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:10,280
Don't leave any evidence behind.

130
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,350
Yes.

131
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:23,690
[Hongyun Tea House]

132
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,530
We sit here with so many people passing by.

133
00:09:02,530 --> 00:09:04,660
It's quite inconvenient to do things.

134
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:06,950
Look.

135
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,340
Here we sit.

136
00:09:10,410 --> 00:09:11,340
What's behind us

137
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:13,900
are residential buildings

138
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,360
which have all been burned down now.

139
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:21,790
No one can hide here.

140
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:24,730
The murderer couldn't be hiding here either.

141
00:09:24,780 --> 00:09:25,790
Look over there.

142
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:28,990
Where?

143
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,160
Hongqi, don't move.

144
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,500
Use your eyes to look.

145
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,030
How can I look without moving?

146
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:44,800
Hongqi.

147
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:47,200
Hongqi.

148
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:49,730
If they don't go around,

149
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:50,860
no one can hide here.

150
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:53,110
The murderer can't hide here.

151
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:55,830
I've already checked before we came in.

152
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:59,120
If the murderer wants to choose the best position,

153
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,180
it can only be that corner of the roof.

154
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:03,000
But that corner of the roof

155
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,590
is blocked by a plant in front.

156
00:10:04,590 --> 00:10:07,220
So this position is a sniper's blind spot.

157
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:26,540
It's safest for us to sit here.

158
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:29,990
What if the murderer

159
00:10:29,990 --> 00:10:32,210
doesn't want to snipe us from a distance?

160
00:10:32,210 --> 00:10:33,520
What it he disguises as an ordinary person

161
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,510
and sneaks into the tea house

162
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:35,990
or waits for us somewhere

163
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:36,650
near the tea house,

164
00:10:36,650 --> 00:10:38,480
trying to take us at close range?

165
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,010
Impossible.

166
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,630
We called at 7:30.

167
00:10:41,810 --> 00:10:43,790
The meeting with the reporter is at 8:30.

168
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:45,760
The murderer only has an hour.

169
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:47,950
When he got the news,

170
00:10:48,210 --> 00:10:50,030
he had to get here as soon as he can.

171
00:10:50,030 --> 00:10:50,670
After he arrived,

172
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:53,520
he needed to observe everything here immediately.

173
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,640
He didn't have time to make a thorough

174
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,410
close-range shot plan without being exposed.

175
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,030
His only plan is remote sniping.

176
00:11:03,380 --> 00:11:04,820
What if

177
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,090
he waits for us to leave

178
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,130
and then snipes us from a distance?

179
00:11:10,190 --> 00:11:11,150
Once we're out,

180
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,550
there won't be any blind spots anymore.

181
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:13,140
Hongqi,

182
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,240
that's a safe option,

183
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:17,980
but the problem is he doesn't know us.

184
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:21,380
He can't see the entire second floor from the roof.

185
00:11:22,460 --> 00:11:25,190
If he wants to know everything, he'll have to enter the teahouse.

186
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:26,640
If he enters the teahouse,

187
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,840
there won't be any long-range sniping.

188
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:31,510
The place we're sitting

189
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:33,110
is the closest to the stairs.

190
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:34,010
Once there are people coming up,

191
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:36,090
we can see everyone clearly.

192
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:40,710
But the murderer won't come up here.

193
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:43,780
He just needs to stand in that position and look up,

194
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:46,220
and he can see the general location of us.

195
00:11:46,490 --> 00:11:47,280
So,

196
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:49,790
this is an essential skill for a professional killer.

197
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,480
The two of us,

198
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,800
dressed up sneakily.

199
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:53,240
Even a ghost would know

200
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:54,840
we're not here to drink tea.

201
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:57,580
I see.

202
00:11:58,570 --> 00:11:59,970
So this murderer's

203
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,540
purpose for entering the teahouse

204
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:03,020
is to identify the target,

205
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,500
then return to the rooftop

206
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:06,120
to snipe us from a distance.

207
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:08,360
I won't let him have the chance.

208
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:10,870
As soon as he comes upstairs, we'll run out.

209
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:13,210
When he's trying to lock onto the target,

210
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,000
we'll take him out.

211
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:17,040
But you don't know what he looks like.

212
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:19,080
How can you be sure who the killer is?

213
00:12:22,590 --> 00:12:23,480
He'll arrive here

214
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,230
no later than 8:25.

215
00:12:26,670 --> 00:12:27,390
He should be

216
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,810
a man under 35 years old,

217
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:30,800
with a solitary personality,

218
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,360
who's received professional training,

219
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,420
and travels light.

220
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,640
Don't worry,

221
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:36,690
A killer has a killer vibe.

222
00:12:37,450 --> 00:12:38,650
As soon as he appears,

223
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,360
I'll be able to recognize him.

224
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:18,660
Shen!

225
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:05,520
How are you?

226
00:14:06,070 --> 00:14:06,590
Hongqi,

227
00:14:06,590 --> 00:14:07,520
I'm really fine.

228
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:24,140
Today is the seventh day since Dad's passing.

229
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:35,790
[Ancient Lushan Temple]

230
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:02,990
Dad.

231
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:05,740
Your son

232
00:15:06,990 --> 00:15:08,230
is here to see you.

233
00:16:01,990 --> 00:16:02,790
Bow.

234
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:07,730
Dad,

235
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:09,880
why do you sometimes

236
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:12,810
place sunflowers in front of this tombstone,

237
00:16:13,050 --> 00:16:14,590
and other times chrysanthemums?

238
00:16:14,590 --> 00:16:16,320
Is there any meaning behind it?

239
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:19,250
Chrysanthemums are for the deceased;

240
00:16:19,630 --> 00:16:21,030
they're more sorrowful.

241
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:23,170
Sunflowers

242
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,410
represent sunshine and hope,

243
00:16:25,850 --> 00:16:26,730
just like every

244
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:30,420
soldier fighting on the battlefield against Japanese invasion.

245
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:32,470
If one day

246
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,280
I'm the one lying here,

247
00:16:36,290 --> 00:16:38,390
don't forget to bring me a bunch of sunflowers.

248
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:38,990
Dad.

249
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:48,790
Hongshen.

250
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,150
Since you've returned to Changsha,

251
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:51,950
from now on,

252
00:16:52,270 --> 00:16:54,730
I'll look after you on behalf of your father.

253
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:00,010
[Hall of Kshitigarbha]

254
00:16:59,150 --> 00:16:59,950
Muzhi,

255
00:17:00,780 --> 00:17:03,640
only when saying goodbye to a true comrade-in-arms

256
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:07,520
do we place a bunch of sunflowers on their gravestone.

257
00:17:07,819 --> 00:17:09,680
Always cherishing hope and light

258
00:17:10,390 --> 00:17:11,950
is our shared wish.

259
00:17:12,819 --> 00:17:13,970
My father once said

260
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:17,780
that you two had a bond forged in life and death.

261
00:17:19,369 --> 00:17:21,430
So you were truly comrades-in-arms.

262
00:17:22,369 --> 00:17:24,700
Being able to fight side by side with Muzhi

263
00:17:24,869 --> 00:17:27,190
is the greatest joy of my life.

264
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:28,860
It's just a pity

265
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:31,810
that he left us too soon.

266
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,320
It's all my fault.

267
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:40,320
My father died because of me.

268
00:17:41,530 --> 00:17:42,410
Your father...

269
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:47,210
was a true warrior.

270
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:52,890
Uncle Yang.

271
00:17:52,890 --> 00:17:53,600
Hongshen,

272
00:17:53,890 --> 00:17:55,210
you can feel guilty,

273
00:17:56,170 --> 00:17:58,640
but you can't let your guilt crush yourself.

274
00:17:59,290 --> 00:18:00,080
Understand?

275
00:18:01,490 --> 00:18:02,290
I understand.

276
00:18:04,010 --> 00:18:04,810
Uncle Yang,

277
00:18:07,490 --> 00:18:08,680
I want to join you.

278
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:10,910
I want to become your comrade.

279
00:18:11,810 --> 00:18:12,890
My father also said

280
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:16,650
when the time is right,

281
00:18:17,410 --> 00:18:19,200
he would let me truly join you.

282
00:18:19,730 --> 00:18:20,880
This was his wish,

283
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:22,960
and it's my wish too.

284
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:29,370
